    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{r^{2}-9r+20}{r-1}} \cdot {\frac{3r-3}{r-4}} =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>3\mathopen{}\left(r-5\right), r\ne 4\hbox{ and }r\ne 1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{r^{2}-9r+20}{r-1}} \cdot {\frac{3r-3}{r-4}} 
      \amp = \frac{{\left(r-4\right)\mathopen{}\left(r-5\right)}}{{r-1}} \cdot \frac{{3\mathopen{}\left(r-1\right)}}{{r-4}} \\
      \amp = {3\mathopen{}\left(r-5\right), r\ne 4\hbox{ and }r\ne 1}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>r - 4</m> and <m>r - 1</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>r \ne {4, 1}</m>.</p>
</solution>
